<div class="content-section">
<h2>The services, in depth</h2>

<div class="provider-card featured">
<div class="provider-header">
<div>
<div class="provider-name">Superpower</div>
<div class="provider-tagline">Best entry-level longevity panel</div>
</div>
<div class="provider-price">
<div class="provider-price-number">$199</div>
<div class="provider-price-label">/ year · 1 draw</div>
</div>
</div>
<p class="provider-body">Superpower covers the longevity fundamentals &#8212; <a href="/biomarkers/apob">ApoB</a>, full hormone panel (testosterone, estradiol, DHEA-S, SHBG), thyroid (TSH + free T3/T4), inflammatory markers (<a href="/biomarkers/hscrp">hsCRP</a>, <a href="/biomarkers/homocysteine">homocysteine</a>), nutritional status (<a href="/biomarkers/vitamin-d">Vitamin D</a>, B12, <a href="/biomarkers/ferritin">ferritin</a>), and complete metabolic and CBC panels &#8212; at the lowest price in the market. The AI dashboard is polished, results come with plain-language explanations, and the biological age score gives you a concrete number to optimize toward. One honest caveat: some of the advertised &#8220;100+ biomarkers&#8221; include algorithmically derived ratios rather than direct measurements &#8212; the subject of a pending lawsuit filed by Function Health in January 2026. <a href="/biomarkers/lipoprotein-a">Lp(a)</a> and omega-3 index require add-ons.</p>
<div class="provider-specs">
<div class="provider-spec"><strong>1</strong>Annual draws</div>
<div class="provider-spec"><strong>100+</strong>Biomarkers (150 w/ratios)</div>
<div class="provider-spec"><strong>3,000+</strong>Quest draw locations</div>
<div class="provider-spec"><strong>NY/NJ</strong>$399/yr</div>
</div>
<a href="https://superpower.com/welcome?dub_id=d99GM8QoZlGRZs2y" target="_blank" rel="noopener sponsored" class="provider-cta">Get Started &#8594;</a>
<a href="/reviews/superpower-health" class="provider-cta secondary">Full Review &#8594;</a>
</div>

<div class="provider-card">
<div class="provider-header">
<div>
<div class="provider-name">Function Health</div>
<div class="provider-tagline">Best comprehensive panel for active management</div>
</div>
<div class="provider-price">
<div class="provider-price-number">$365</div>
<div class="provider-price-label">/ year · 2 draws</div>
</div>
</div>
<p class="provider-body">Function Health is the most thorough consumer biomarker service at a non-concierge price. Two annual draws, 160+ directly measured markers, cancer screening markers (PSA, CEA, AFP, CA-125), heavy metals (lead, mercury, arsenic), ANA autoimmune screen, and <a href="/biomarkers/lipoprotein-a">Lp(a)</a> and <a href="/biomarkers/omega-3-index">omega-3 index</a> included in the base panel. The twice-yearly cadence is the key differentiator &#8212; the only service in this price range that enables a test-intervene-retest loop within a single membership year. Trade-offs: no historical lab import, the AI protocol builder is newer than Superpower&#8217;s, and there is no home draw option. Founded by Dr. Mark Hyman and backed by $298M in Series B funding.</p>
<div class="provider-specs">
<div class="provider-spec"><strong>2</strong>Annual draws</div>
<div class="provider-spec"><strong>160+</strong>Direct biomarkers</div>
<div class="provider-spec"><strong>$365</strong>Reduced from $499</div>
<div class="provider-spec"><strong>NY/NJ/RI</strong>Not available</div>
</div>
<a href="https://functionhealth.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="provider-cta secondary">Visit Function Health &#8594;</a>
<a href="/reviews/function-health" class="provider-cta secondary">Full Review &#8594;</a>
</div>

<div class="provider-card">
<div class="provider-header">
<div>
<div class="provider-name">InsideTracker</div>
<div class="provider-tagline">Best for athletic optimization and DNA integration</div>
</div>
<div class="provider-price">
<div class="provider-price-number">$149&#8211;$489</div>
<div class="provider-price-label">/ year · varies by tier</div>
</div>
</div>
<p class="provider-body">InsideTracker, founded in 2009 by researchers from MIT and Tufts University, was the original direct-to-consumer biomarker platform. Its differentiation today lies in DNA integration (genetic testing layered with blood data), wearable sync (Apple Watch and others), and a legacy of longevity science credibility. The marker breadth is narrower than Function or Superpower &#8212; up to 48 biomarkers on the Ultimate tier &#8212; but the action plan quality and InnerAge biological age calculation are well-regarded. Pricing is tiered and adds up quickly: the $149/year membership covers platform access only; actual testing runs $340&#8211;$489 additional depending on panel. Total annual cost for a serious user is $489&#8211;$638.</p>
<div class="provider-specs">
<div class="provider-spec"><strong>Up to 48</strong>Biomarkers (Ultimate)</div>
<div class="provider-spec"><strong>$489+</strong>Total cost with testing</div>
<div class="provider-spec"><strong>DNA add-on</strong>Available</div>
<div class="provider-spec"><strong>Wearables</strong>Apple Watch + others</div>
</div>
<a href="https://insidetracker.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="provider-cta secondary">Visit InsideTracker &#8594;</a>
</div>

<div class="provider-card">
<div class="provider-header">
<div>
<div class="provider-name">OneTwenty</div>
<div class="provider-tagline">Best continuous care system (beta)</div>
</div>
<div class="provider-price">
<div class="provider-price-number">$499</div>
<div class="provider-price-label">/ year · quarterly draws</div>
</div>
</div>
<p class="provider-body">OneTwenty (formerly Outlive.bio) is the most integrated option in this comparison &#8212; less a pure testing service and more a continuous health optimization system. The $499/year Core membership includes quarterly biomarker testing (78 markers at baseline, then 20&#8211;40 targeted markers every 90 days), AI health coaching, wearable data integration (syncing continuous signals from Oura, Whoop, Apple Watch), and access to affiliated physicians who can prescribe when warranted. It is currently in beta, with full launch expected July 2026. The quarterly testing cadence is meaningful: it&#8217;s the only service that enables rapid intervention tracking. Trade-offs: newer platform with less track record, beta-stage product polish, and prescription access varies by state.</p>
<div class="provider-specs">
<div class="provider-spec"><strong>4</strong>Quarterly draws</div>
<div class="provider-spec"><strong>78 baseline</strong>+ targeted markers</div>
<div class="provider-spec"><strong>Rx access</strong>Via affiliated physicians</div>
<div class="provider-spec"><strong>Beta</strong>Full launch July 2026</div>
</div>
<a href="https://onetwenty.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="provider-cta secondary">Visit OneTwenty &#8594;</a>
</div>

<div class="provider-card">
<div class="provider-header">
<div>
<div class="provider-name">Marek Health</div>
<div class="provider-tagline">Best for clinical optimization with physician oversight</div>
</div>
<div class="provider-price">
<div class="provider-price-number">$450&#8211;$2,000</div>
<div class="provider-price-label">/ draw · à la carte</div>
</div>
</div>
<p class="provider-body">Marek Health is a different category from the services above &#8212; a telehealth clinical optimization practice, not a pure testing subscription. Founded by Derek from More Plates More Dates on the premise that you cannot optimize what you do not measure, Marek pairs comprehensive LabCorp panels with physician and health coach oversight and the ability to prescribe treatments (TRT, peptides, GLP-1s, thyroid, and more). Four panel tiers: Base ($250), Comprehensive ($450), Complete ($850), and Executive ($2,000). A key technical differentiator: Marek uses LC/MS (liquid chromatography-mass spectrometry) for testosterone and estradiol &#8212; significantly more accurate than standard immunoassays, particularly important for women and anyone on hormone therapy. Annual costs for a managed patient easily reach $1,000&#8211;$2,500 between panels and consultation fees. Right for someone who wants a clinician actively managing their optimization protocol. Not the right fit if you just want data.</p>
<div class="provider-specs">
<div class="provider-spec"><strong>On-demand</strong>No annual commitment</div>
<div class="provider-spec"><strong>LC/MS</strong>Higher-accuracy hormones</div>
<div class="provider-spec"><strong>Rx access</strong>TRT, peptides, GLP-1</div>
<div class="provider-spec"><strong>47 states</strong>Not NY/NJ/RI</div>
