<div class="content-section">
<h2>How to choose</h2>

<h3>Start here if you&#8217;ve never done comprehensive testing</h3>
<p><strong>Superpower at $199/year</strong> is the right entry point for most people in this situation. It covers the markers that matter most for longevity &#8212; <a href="/biomarkers/apob">ApoB</a>, full hormone panel, thyroid, inflammatory markers, nutritional status &#8212; at a price that makes it easy to commit. The biological age score and polished dashboard make results easy to act on. You can always upgrade to Function Health after you have a baseline and understand what you want to track more closely.</p>

<h3>Choose Function Health if you&#8217;re actively managing your health</h3>
<p>The twice-yearly draw is what separates Function from everything in its price range. If you&#8217;re working on a specific cardiovascular marker, adjusting hormone protocols, or supplementing based on deficiencies, the mid-year retest is the only way to know whether anything worked within a single year. Function also belongs at the top of the list for anyone who wants cancer marker screening or heavy metal testing as part of their annual workup.</p>

<h3>Choose OneTwenty if you want a full system, not just data</h3>
<p>OneTwenty is built around the idea that testing alone isn&#8217;t enough &#8212; what matters is continuous feedback and guided action. If you want quarterly testing, AI coaching that integrates your wearable data, and physician access for prescription optimization, OneTwenty is the most complete product in this space. The caveat is that it&#8217;s still in beta as of mid-2026, and newer platforms carry product maturity risk.</p>

<h3>Choose InsideTracker if you&#8217;re performance-focused</h3>
<p>InsideTracker&#8217;s strengths are its athletic performance orientation, its DNA add-on (which layers genetic data with blood results for more personalized recommendations), and its wearable integrations. If you&#8217;re training seriously and want a platform built around performance optimization rather than longevity risk reduction, InsideTracker is the best fit. Be aware that the total annual cost including testing is $489&#8211;$638 &#8212; higher than the membership price alone suggests.</p>

<h3>Choose Marek Health if you want clinical management, not just data</h3>
<p>Marek Health is for someone who wants a physician actively involved in interpreting results and prescribing protocols &#8212; TRT, peptides, thyroid optimization, or GLP-1 weight management. The testing panels are excellent and the LC/MS hormone methodology is more accurate than what subscription services use. But the annual cost is substantially higher, and the model works best for someone already committed to an active optimization protocol.</p>

<h3>Use Ulta Lab Tests for flexibility and frequency</h3>
<p>If you already know which markers you want, if you need to test more than twice per year, or if you want to verify specific results from another service, Ulta Lab Tests is the right tool. There is no dashboard or interpretation layer &#8212; results come raw. Pair it with our <a href="/analyze">AI biomarker interpreter</a> to get longevity-optimal range analysis on whatever you order.</p>

<div class="warning-callout">
<div class="warning-callout-label">State availability</div>
<p>Most of these services are unavailable or priced differently in New York, New Jersey, and Rhode Island due to state regulations on direct-to-consumer lab testing. Superpower charges $399/year (vs. $199) in NY and NJ. Function Health, InsideTracker, and Ulta Lab Tests are generally not available in those states. Marek Health operates in 47 states. Confirm availability at each service&#8217;s website before purchasing.</p>
</div>
